Aspect Model Simulated Capacity Group

urn:samm:io.catenax.simulated_week_based_capacity_group:1.0.0#SimulatedWeekBasedCapacityGroup
An entity that can contain multiple WeekBasedCapacityGroup in addition to the evaluation of a simulation scenario, requested by the customer.

Simulation Status

The simulation status indicates whether the supplier will actively work on a simulation scenario (ACCEPTED) or not (REJECTED). In addition it can indicate the outcome of a simulation, as scenario could be implemented (SUCCESS) or scenario cannot be implemented (FAILURE). Finally it can acknowledge that the customer has aborted the simulation scenario (ABORTED).
Name
simulationStatus
Characteristic
Enumeration
Werte
  • ACCEPTED
  • REJECTED
  • ABORTED
  • SUCCESS
  • FAILURE
Typ http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string
Beispiel
ACCEPTED
Optional

Maximum Capacity
The supplier maximum capacity is the maximal available output per calendar week and material for a specific customer in a specific unit of measure. The maximum capacity thereby restricts the flexible capacity, as the flexible capacity is obtained from the difference of a suppliers maximum capacity minus actual capacity.

Unit Of Measure Is Omitted
Explicit indicator of whether the unit of measure is left out of the payload intentionally. If "true" it means the sending application sends demand values without unit of measure intentionally and the unit of measure MUST NOT be contained in the payload. If "false" a unit of measure MUST be supplied.
